Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.50,0:00:05.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Star" is a fascinating word.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.96,0:00:07.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can refer to both culprits and actors!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.50,0:00:09.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,During the big adventure at the Karakuri Mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.17,0:00:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We come across some surprisingly life-threatening traps...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.80,0:00:12.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the Detective Boys work together\Nto outwit that conceited sneak-thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.76,0:00:14.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing through to the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.43,0:00:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look like a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.01,0:00:18.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.21,0:00:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we felt the same light the moment we met.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.10,0:00:29.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, lots and lots of the same emotions filled our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.85,0:00:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although the signals you sent destroyed my theory...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.75,0:00:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These feelings were always beyond your reach
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.74,0:00:47.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, let's fight, go against our morals...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.78,0:00:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And aim for a wider world!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.30,0:00:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, glimmering star, shine over us forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.15,0:01:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, we won't lose the dreams we had when we were young...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.13,0:01:11.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't care if this town changes someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.10,0:01:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing I don't want to change is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.20,0:01:23.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, glimmering star, shine over us forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.90,0:01:29.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, we won't lose the dreams we had when we were young...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:39.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing I don't want to change is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.49,0:01:48.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the melody of "Seven Children", I figured out the\Ne-mail address belonging to the boss of the men in black.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.37,0:01:52.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But according to Haibara,\Nwe mustn't proceed any further with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.19,0:01:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, Genta and the others who\Ncame to camp with us discovered a strange stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.18,0:02:03.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inside, we found a coded\Nmessage leading to the "Big Jewel"...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.68,0:02:07.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And right next to it, we found the\Nbody of a man who had been murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.71,0:02:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The stone that will fill one's hand to the fullest"?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.13,0:02:16.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.51,0:02:18.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you find? Tell us!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.34,0:02:24.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hand... Fill to the fullest...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.36,0:02:25.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Big Jewel!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.98,0:02:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no mistaking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.76,0:02:45.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Big Adventure at the Unconventional Mansion:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.97,0:02:47.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Karakuri Part!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.68,0:02:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.48,0:02:59.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sure looks like this is the start of\N"Diamond Cut Diamond", doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.31,0:03:01.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.99,0:03:04.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A Belgian proverb.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.35,0:03:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know that the only thing that can\Ncut a diamond is another diamond, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.00,0:03:13.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Likewise, this is the beginning of an all-out\Nwar between two equally level-headed people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.29,0:03:18.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But exactly who are the ones that are fighting?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.30,0:03:22.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.88,0:03:26.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Neither him nor I are something as grandiose as a diamond.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.56,0:03:30.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy is someone covering up\Nthe truth with a veil for the heck of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.56,0:03:31.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A simple thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.77,0:03:36.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While I'm itching to rip off that unsightly veil...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.92,0:03:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A simple detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.49,0:03:45.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Who's this "thief" you're talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.87,0:03:49.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that he's talking about the\Npartner of this guy, who had drowned in the lake?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.58,0:03:56.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I'm talking about the guy who's\Nobsessed with stealing large jewels like "Big Jewel"...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.04,0:03:58.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one known as "Kaitou Kid."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.05,0:03:59.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That conceited scoundrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.55,0:04:00.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ka...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.55,0:04:02.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaitou Kid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.68,0:04:04.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.68,0:04:07.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We know that name!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.76,0:04:10.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The kind-hearted one who comes and goes with a bang...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.18,0:04:11.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The gentleman thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.89,0:04:14.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard from the Professor...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.31,0:04:16.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About this never-ending fight you're both involved in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.31,0:04:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Never-ending fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.94,0:04:21.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you have the feeling that you're always losing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.19,0:04:24.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I don't ever lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.49,0:04:26.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's never succeeded in getting\Naway with the treasure, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.20,0:04:29.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, is Kid going to come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.95,0:04:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said that's only a possibility, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.58,0:04:36.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you remember what that guy wrote in his notebook?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.54,0:04:39.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"This way, I will finally outwit this conceited sneak-thief."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.92,0:04:44.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"This conceited sneak-thief" is probably referring to Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.55,0:04:47.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that guy was murdered by...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.68,0:04:49.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kid did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.81,0:04:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.39,0:04:55.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rumors say that he never resorting to killing, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.44,0:05:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Kid, or the culprit behind\Nthat guy's murder, must be close by.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.44,0:05:05.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly, since they still haven't\Nfound the treasure they're after.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.45,0:05:10.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means the answer must lie inside that mansion, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.75,0:05:18.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since it started to rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.38,0:05:21.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't we go in the mansion\Nand take a quick look until it calms down?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.30,0:05:22.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.17,0:05:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.01,0:05:24.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The treasure hunt...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.46,0:05:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is starting, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.93,0:05:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't get the wrong idea, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.68,0:05:31.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's only until the Professor comes back with the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.47,0:05:34.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.05,0:06:11.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now that we're about to enter the mansion,\NI've noticed just how depressing it looks...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.76,0:06:14.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there really a treasure inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.10,0:06:18.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that a treasure is hidden somewhere around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.69,0:06:20.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I noticed it earlier, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.90,0:06:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's fresh mud along the point where\Nthe wall meets the foundation of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.28,0:06:29.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it looks like it continues around the entire perimeter...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.91,0:06:31.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.82,0:06:33.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.03,0:06:37.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell us what that thing back there meant again!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.16,0:06:40.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's talking about the meaning of the\Ntext carved inside the Japanese stone lantern.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.12,0:06:42.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.96,0:06:46.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure the Two Kings weren't here, were they?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.34,0:06:48.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.05,0:06:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The resting place of the Two Kings,\Nnear to that which brings life..."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.30,0:06:54.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"At the place where the elders gather,\Nfull of prosperity and vitality."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.97,0:06:56.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"There, you will find the Two Kings' Stone."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.93,0:06:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The person who does not\Nfear the wrath of the Two Kings..."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.98,0:07:03.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Shall acquire the knowledge of the eternal truth..."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.11,0:07:05.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"In order to take possession of the\Nstone that will fill one's hand to the fullest."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.98,0:07:07.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Samizu Kichiemon."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.94,0:07:13.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you interpret it figuratively, it says the place where\Nthe Two Kings are resting is the closest place to the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.56,0:07:16.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's a very busting place where the elders meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.66,0:07:18.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And "There, you will find the Two Kings' Stone."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.91,0:07:22.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's where the diamond is hidden, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.79,0:07:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what's intriguing are the words that come after that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.96,0:07:28.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.01,0:07:31.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's fine and all, but Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} stopped\Nexplaining, so I don't understand what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.97,0:07:35.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The person who does not\Nfear the wrath of the Two Kings..."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.10,0:07:38.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"In order to take possession of the\Nstone that will fill one's hand to the fullest..."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.43,0:07:41.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"You must understand its origin, from long ago."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.77,0:07:44.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.48,0:07:46.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the Two Kings really will get angry...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.82,0:07:48.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.03,0:07:51.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then there's the thing we found\Nin the cuff of that guy's pants earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.28,0:07:54.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The comma-shaped, magatama stone\Nengraved with the character for flame.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.45,0:07:58.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What connection does this have with the coded message?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.08,0:07:59.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I still don't understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.33,0:08:01.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.04,0:08:02.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, why don't we just go in?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.79,0:08:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know, don't rush!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.25,0:08:08.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there anything else written in\Nthe notebook that guy had on him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.88,0:08:11.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is something else written here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.13,0:08:14.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we can't read it because it's all wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.55,0:08:16.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We might be able to if we wait for it to dry, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.39,0:08:18.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't wait that long!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.43,0:08:21.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.61,0:08:27.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.40,0:08:29.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't enter so carelessly!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.86,0:08:32.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This mansion was built by Karakuri Kichiemon, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.03,0:08:38.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The diamond is at the closest place to the sun, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.24,0:08:42.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why it has to be at the very\Ntop of this mansion, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.13,0:08:51.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First off, let's go to the highest place!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.38,0:08:55.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Wait, Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.59,0:08:59.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I move softly, everything will be okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.31,0:09:00.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.44,0:09:06.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.02,0:09:07.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.45,0:09:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.00,0:09:29.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here, brats?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.25,0:09:33.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.00,0:09:36.21,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Satou Unzou (40)\NTreasure Hunter
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.55,0:09:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you guys also looking for Kichiemon's treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.34,0:09:38.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.18,0:09:40.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.47,0:09:42.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look out for yourselves in the future, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.35,0:09:44.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These stairs are a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.48,0:09:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to go upstairs, you\Nhave to think more outside of the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.44,0:09:56.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Karakuri Kichiemon was quite the jokester.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.49,0:10:01.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if you take the most obvious approach you see,\Nhoping to get what you're after, you're going to get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.91,0:10:05.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides that, did you guys\Nhappen to find a odd-looking stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.20,0:10:06.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, about that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.83,0:10:09.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't find it! Or anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.21,0:10:09.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.17,0:10:12.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.17,0:10:14.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well... If you find it, let me know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.76,0:10:15.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.71,0:10:16.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.55,0:10:18.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.80,0:10:21.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you lie to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.35,0:10:24.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He saved Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, so he has to be a nice person!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.81,0:10:29.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't know if he's actually a nice person...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.27,0:10:33.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a possibility he's just acting friendly towards us\Nto get his hands on the comma-shaped magatama stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.07,0:10:34.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.57,0:10:37.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd definitely act like that if he was Kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.57,0:10:40.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or even if he's the culprit behind the\Nmurder of that guy we found earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.66,0:10:46.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But right now, it seems he knows a lot about this mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.58,0:10:49.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it'd be better if we stuck with him for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.58,0:10:52.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially in order to prevent him\Nfrom escaping before the police arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.58,0:10:57.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, did the Professor already call the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.80,0:11:01.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it further in?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.89,0:11:04.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This "old, run down mansion"...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.43,0:11:06.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.35,0:11:10.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's completely black up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.27,0:11:10.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.77,0:11:11.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.36,0:11:16.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which way was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.11,0:11:17.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.41,0:11:22.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's carp!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.86,0:11:24.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's a whole bunch of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.49,0:11:29.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having a river flowing through the house\Nmakes it look like a high-class restaurant, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.45,0:11:32.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's connected with the lake outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.17,0:11:36.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look! There's a bridge, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.85,0:11:48.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A trap?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.90,0:11:57.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I won't fall for that this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.90,0:12:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, actually it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.97,0:12:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.26,0:12:29.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like an elevator, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.14,0:12:32.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.81,0:12:35.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and get on!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.35,0:12:36.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.19,0:12:44.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this means that we have to go down to get up...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.45,0:12:48.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that if we go up, we end\Nup falling back down, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.03,0:12:50.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once we understand the trick, it's really easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.29,0:12:50.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure is!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.25,0:12:56.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like we arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.46,0:13:00.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was so easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.68,0:13:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fools...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.05,0:13:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If things were that simple, we wouldn't\Neven have to bother looking for the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.00,0:13:13.51,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Akutsu Sarina (29)\NTreasure Hunter
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.93,0:13:13.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Kid-Taking-Treasure-Hunter{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.44,0:13:19.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't take these brats with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.86,0:13:23.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, even if they are brats...\NWhat were you thinking, throwing a knife at them?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.57,0:13:26.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a good look at the knife's blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.99,0:13:28.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A poisonous spider!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.99,0:13:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This "Kichiemon" person is not just a jokester,\Nbut also extremely malicious, wouldn't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.08,0:13:37.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're trying to get to the\Nhighest point in the house, it's this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.42,0:13:41.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that this older lady is Kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.75,0:13:44.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't Kid a guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.09,0:13:47.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. I heard he sometimes\Ndisguises himself as a young woman, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.43,0:13:55.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, and watch your step, brats...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.27,0:13:57.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Cause some of those deadly spiders are still around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.15,0:14:02.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.99,0:14:09.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.99,0:14:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and get up here...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.12,0:14:12.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or you'll get bitten by a poisonous spider!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.29,0:14:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'll go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.79,0:14:24.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, look! We reached the highest place!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.21,0:14:27.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's nothing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.09,0:14:29.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, is it on the roof?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.26,0:14:31.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me see, to get on the roof...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.68,0:14:34.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.01,0:14:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why doesn't this floor have a support column?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.48,0:14:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, there it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.94,0:14:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a ladder!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.77,0:14:43.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were some on the previous floors.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.44,0:14:47.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're the first!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.40,0:14:49.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.15,0:14:51.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Knowing the nature of that person,\Nif there's a missing support column...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.49,0:14:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop! That's a trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.58,0:14:56.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.29,0:15:02.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.04,0:15:03.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crap...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.05,0:15:08.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.97,0:15:09.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.72,0:15:10.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.47,0:15:11.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.09,0:15:53.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.05,0:15:55.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sending a rope down to you right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.64,0:15:57.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't we already tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.56,0:16:01.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That if we go up, we end up falling back down...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.45,0:16:14.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is everyone all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.45,0:16:15.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.45,0:16:16.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.24,0:16:17.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.29,0:16:25.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We somehow went down, but it\Nlooks we can't go any lower, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.00,0:16:27.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though we wanted to reach the top...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.34,0:16:31.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I checked the roof, but there's nothing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.01,0:16:32.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.26,0:16:34.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Coming here was probably the right decision...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.18,0:16:38.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.85,0:16:40.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.73,0:16:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Skeletons!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.19,0:16:48.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.86,0:16:49.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.78,0:16:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here... Skeletons!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.23,0:16:52.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over there, over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.62,0:16:59.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Based on how they look, I'd say they were treasure hunters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.91,0:17:00.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.83,0:17:06.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then there's this old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.56,0:17:12.62,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Senju Eri (72)\NTreasure Hunter
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.96,0:17:11.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not an old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.71,0:17:12.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm an old woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.89,0:17:21.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I slept well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.39,0:17:22.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.47,0:17:23.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.60,0:17:26.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this granny is also our rival?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.44,0:17:27.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.11,0:17:30.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you a treasure hunter, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.52,0:17:36.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only came for a little leisure and to\Nvisit a grave so I can pay my respects.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.49,0:17:37.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A grave?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.78,0:17:41.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Kichiemon{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.45,0:17:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Samizu Kichiemon's grave?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.95,0:17:46.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kichiemon's grave?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.58,0:17:49.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be the first to see it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.59,0:17:55.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it keeps going on like this, these kids\Nwill bring the treasure back with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.63,0:18:01.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Wandering person, offer me the\NThree Imperial Regalia. - Samizu Kichiemon."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.68,0:18:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Granny...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.60,0:18:05.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a coded message?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.98,0:18:07.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.60,0:18:10.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought it was saying how to pay your\Nrespects to Kichiemon{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} at his grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.69,0:18:13.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I wonder what it means...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.19,0:18:16.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It tells us something like "offer me something"...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.36,0:18:19.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, we didn't bring food or flowers with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.87,0:18:21.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.70,0:18:25.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing that was hiding in the cuff\Nof the guy who drowned in the lake...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.91,0:18:28.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was a comma-shaped magatama stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.96,0:18:30.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Mister...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.46,0:18:34.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You asked us something earlier, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.13,0:18:36.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You asked, "Did you guys\Nhappen to find a odd-looking stone?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.47,0:18:39.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because you have one, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.47,0:18:41.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A stone related to the Two Kings.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.01,0:18:41.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.43,0:18:45.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, we found one too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.22,0:18:48.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A stone that was created as\None of the Three Imperial Regalia.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.19,0:18:50.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.19,0:18:52.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you tell us that was a secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.52,0:18:54.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was written on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.57,0:18:59.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a some kind of character\Nengraved on the stone you found, wasn't there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.16,0:19:02.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought so! You really did find one, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.79,0:19:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.41,0:19:07.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.83,0:19:13.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think withholding information in\Nthe predicament we're in is a very good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.21,0:19:15.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.75,0:19:20.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you don't want to be excluded from our\Ngroup, hurry and show us what you found.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.89,0:19:23.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.98,0:19:34.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found this stone that looks like a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.56,0:19:38.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eternity\NIt's engraved with the character "ei" from "eien", isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.15,0:19:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, it is really linked to the sun!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.82,0:19:43.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because it's always burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.20,0:19:48.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the comma-shaped magatama you guys found...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.08,0:19:50.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Flame\NWas engraved with "honoo"\Nor something like that, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.83,0:19:52.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.62,0:19:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a great guess, Miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.96,0:19:59.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't understand the\Nmeaning behind "ei" and "honoo".
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.09,0:20:02.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we put these stones in the spaces in the grave...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.55,0:20:04.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We may trigger some\Nmechanism and the Two Kings' stone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.89,0:20:07.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is to say, the diamond may come out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.18,0:20:09.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why do you think that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.98,0:20:11.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.18,0:20:14.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was in the text engraved inside\Nthe Japanese stone lantern, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.73,0:20:18.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The diamond is at a lively\Nplace where older people gather."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.07,0:20:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this what it meant about a\Nlively place where older people gather?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.82,0:20:23.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.99,0:20:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see... What was it again?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.57,0:20:27.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The resting place of the Two Kings..."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.33,0:20:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.24,0:20:31.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The resting place of the Two Kings,\Nnear to that which brings life..."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.62,0:20:36.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"At the place where the elders gather,\Nfull of prosperity and vitality."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.29,0:20:38.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"There, you will find the Two Kings' Stone."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.55,0:20:39.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.42,0:20:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.59,0:20:43.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A lively place where older people gather.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.13,0:20:46.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The place where the elders gather,\Nfull of prosperity and vitality"...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.93,0:20:52.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you honestly think that a such a\Ndescription refers to this mountain of dead corpses?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.23,0:20:53.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.81,0:20:55.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.48,0:21:01.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These people are fools who were blinded by\Ntheir greed, lost their way, and ended up dying here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.74,0:21:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention that when Kichiemon{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nbuilt this mansion, not a single corpse was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.78,0:21:08.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! That sounds about right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.74,0:21:11.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you also saw that Japanese stone lantern, Granny?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.87,0:21:15.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but it wasn't sunk in the lake...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.62,0:21:19.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it doesn't look like the jewel is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.21,0:21:24.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't look like there's a mechanism that would\Nbe triggered by putting the stones in this grave, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.93,0:21:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, we really do have to find one more of\Nthe Three Imperial Regalia to solve this mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.64,0:21:31.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"One more...?"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.27,0:21:34.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The third of the Three Imperial Regalia.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.39,0:21:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We already found the mirror\Nand the comma-shaped magatama...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.90,0:21:39.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So there has to be one more somewhere around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.98,0:21:41.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Three Imperial Regalia?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.19,0:21:43.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.07,0:21:44.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eight Hand Mirror\NThe mirror is known as the "Yata no Kagami"...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.95,0:21:47.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tear of Benevolence\NThe magatama is known as the "Yasakani no Magatama"...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.49,0:21:49.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the last one remaining...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.66,0:21:52.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Long ago, when a treacherous\Nwarlord set a grassy plain on fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.95,0:21:56.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to send Yamato-dake Mikoto to his\Ndemise by trapping him in the ensuing blaze...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.21,0:21:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used a sword to mow the grass...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.92,0:21:59.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ultimately saving himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.29,0:22:01.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the divine sword:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.50,0:22:03.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grass-Mowing Sword\NThe "Kusanagi no Tsurugi".
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.47,0:22:09.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "Kusanagi no Tsurugi"?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.23,0:22:30.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before I knew it, I had come to the riverside of memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.74,0:22:40.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Imagining a continuation of yesterday's dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.96,0:22:47.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You seemed so grown-up when you were a boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.59,0:22:53.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't say goodbye, so I hid under my umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.81,0:22:59.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we ever meet again, just please remember
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.48,0:23:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,all those times, and don't forget me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.98,0:23:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My love and affection are things that will never change.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.24,0:23:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You are my one and only love, and that's how it will always be.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.09,0:23:33.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like many people, I reminisce while holding on to my feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.80,0:23:46.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I can keep the memory of us meeting from fading away.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.03,0:23:51.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.95,0:23:57.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Wandering person, offer me the Three Imperial Regalia."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.42,0:24:10.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise this water is going to sweep us away,\Nall the way down to the bottom of the valley!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.60,0:24:11.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.97,0:24:15.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Big Adventure at the Unconventional Mansion, Solution Part.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.86,0:24:18.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.50,0:24:20.90,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: Kekanbi is the name of a Frankenstein-like\Nmonster dog in a Japanese horror movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.24,0:24:19.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Kekanbi!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.32,0:24:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Samizu Kichiemon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.03,0:24:26.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\b1}Please look forward to the next episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.04,0:24:25.47,Signs,,0,0,0,,By itself, "mon" means gate, while "emon" used\Nto be common ending for a male's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.31,0:24:22.63,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What type of gate is Kichiemon?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.64,0:24:23.53,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.56,0:24:24.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's a person's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.61,0:24:25.47,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And an ordinary one at that...
